ysics, and Marxist-Leninist theories of language —on the monumental aesthetic and political shifts of the early twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAzerbaijani literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aCaucasian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aInsurgency in literature. 0aPoeticsxHistoryy20th century. 0aRussian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aHistory. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aSoviet & East European History.  aEurasianism, global avant-garde, Turkic Poetry, Caucasus, influence of Soviet anti-imperial revolution on literature, Muslim communist consciousness, contemporary geopolitics, Azeri revolutionary poets, Soviet Orientalism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060655308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishz978311060418408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2018z9783110603187oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501726514?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501726514423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501726514/original  a978-3-11-060418-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-D